AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION!!! Meet Patches an adorable 1-2 year old Lab/Terrier mix. Patches has an incredibly sweet disposition. She is an easy going girl that loves everyone she meet. Patches was recently rescued from an area shelter and is adjusting wonderfully in her foster home. She is very smart girl that is very eager to please. She already knows commands like sit, stay and lay down. She is good on the leash and is a joy to walk. She is house and crate trained. If you looking for a new addition to your family or just a loyal companion look no further Patches is the girl for you. She is spayed, current on vaccines and microchipped. She currently weighs 45lbs and is full grown. Patches is ready and waiting to meet her forever family. Pounce de Leon was part of a horrific hoarding case in Tempe. Thankfully, he was able to be saved. This boy is quiet and reserved however will gladly soak up all the attention from his family once he knows he's home and safe forever. He would be the perfect only cat if you are looking for a solo kitty but could also share space willingly. His loyalty is unwavering and hopes yours will be too. Pounce loves the laser light and of course, any toys with bells or a bit of cat nip.

Meet Shawnee!
Shawnee has a sweet, soft face and a gentle personality to match! She enjoys going for walks with her person, walking elegantly by your side as you explore the neighborhood. As a German Shepherd dog, it's no surprise this girl is also a smarty who loves to work for.. treats! She knows Sit, 'Find it', and comes when called. Shawnee also likes to play fetch-- though her version is taken at a leisurely pace and she seems to enjoy relaxing and chewing the ball more
(**Scroll to see video!) 😉
.
Shawnee came into the shelter on Oct 21, 2017 as an Owner Surrender. No reason for surrender was given, but they did report that she is housebroken, is friendly with small dogs (though fought with her GSD sibling), and is okay in the car and on leash. Shawnee is 5 years old and 85 pounds.
This lovable, friendly girl is ready to join a family on a lifetime of adventures- come meet her today!
💖 Shawnee #A1736835 🐾
*Blue/ Medically Alerted for possible solar dermatitis (on nose).*
----------------------

@Regranned from @the_stinky_crew - TAFFY has been homeless 15 months and counting! Please SHARE to show you care she finds a family! 💞

Taffy is a cheerful sweetheart who is as delightful as soft candy. She is treat-motivated and already knows “sit” and “shake”. She would make a good companion on long walks, hiking trips or just hanging out at home. When we had her in the yard, she wasn’t keen on meeting the other dogs so we think she would prefer a home where she can be top dog. If you’re looking for an outgoing girl who loves people, please consider our sweet Taffy or TAG, COMMENT & SHARE her story to help her find a home to call her own!

Taffy is a 3 years old, spayed white and tan Pit Bull Terrier Taffy who has been at the shelter since October 11, 2016.

TAFFY #A1661820 💗🍭

TAFFY has been homeless 15 months and counting! Please SHARE to show you care she finds a family! 💞

Taffy is a cheerful sweetheart who is as delightful as soft candy. She is treat-motivated and already knows “sit” and “shake”. She would make a good companion on long walks, hiking trips or just hanging out at home. When we had her in the yard, she wasn’t keen on meeting the other dogs so we think she would prefer a home where she can be top dog. If you’re looking for an outgoing girl who loves people, please consider our sweet Taffy or TAG, COMMENT & SHARE her story to help her find a home to call her own!

Taffy is a 3 years old, spayed white and tan Pit Bull Terrier Taffy who has been at the shelter since October 11, 2016.

AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION!!! Meet Lenny, a Boxer mix born around June 2017. Lenny is an absolute sweetheart. He is such a good boy with a great disposition. He was recently rescued from and area shelter after being found emaciated. He is currently in a foster home and doing very well. Lenny is a loyal companion that will stay by your side. He is a playful boy that gets along with other dogs wonderfully. He is very treat motivated and is catching on quickly to basic commands. He walks well on leash, is great in the crate and house trained. Lenny currently weighs 37lbs and will weigh around 50lbs full grown. He is current on vaccines, microchipped and will be neutered on January 23rd 2018. His is best suited in a home with children 5 years old or older. Meet Shawnee!
Shawnee has a sweet, soft face and a gentle personality to match! She enjoys going for walks with her person, walking elegantly by your side as you explore the neighborhood. As a German Shepherd dog, it's no surprise this girl is also a smarty who loves to work for.. treats! She knows Sit, 'Find it', and comes when called. Shawnee also likes to play fetch-- though her version is taken at a leisurely pace and she seems to enjoy relaxing and chewing the ball more
(**Scroll to see video!) 😉
.
Shawnee came into the shelter on Oct 21, 2017 as an Owner Surrender. No reason for surrender was given, but they did report that she is housebroken, is friendly with small dogs (though fought with her GSD sibling), and is okay in the car and on leash. Shawnee is 5 years old and 85 pounds.
This lovable, friendly girl is ready to join a family on a lifetime of adventures- come meet her today!
💖 Shawnee #A1736835 🐾
